FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1779196276
OL,3,CDemonstration against scrapping of
OL,4,Cjury trials takes place
OL,6,FFiona Atkinson was at the protest. She
OL,7,Ftold ITV Border: "It's absolutely
OL,8,Foutrageous that the Government should
OL,9,Fbe reducing the rights and freedoms of
OL,10,Fordinary people.
OL,12,F"For 800 years British people have had
OL,13,Fthe right to be tried by a jury. To
OL,14,Ftake that away from us at a time when
OL,15,Fpeople already feel discounted and
OL,16,Fignored is totally unacceptable."
OL,18,FThe changes to the justice system were
OL,19,Ffirst announced in December 2025 by
OL,20,FJustice Secretary David Lammy to help
OL,21,Ftackle court waiting times.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1779196276
OL,3,CDemonstration against scrapping of
OL,4,Cjury trials takes place
OL,6,FAt the time he told the Commons he
OL,7,Fwants to "deliver the swifter justice
OL,8,Fvictims deserve" as the crown courts
OL,9,Fface a 78,000-strong backlog.
OL,11,FThe Government has since continued to
OL,12,Fpush its Courts and Tribunals Bill
OL,13,Fthrough.
OL,15,FOn the importance of jury trials, Ms
OL,16,FAtkinson said: "The jury is so
OL,17,Fimportant as it's about the views and
OL,18,Fvoices of ordinary people.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1779196276
OL,3,CDemonstration against scrapping of
OL,4,Cjury trials takes place
OL,6,F"Personally, if I was going to be in a
OL,7,Ftrial judged by a single judge, I
OL,8,Fdon't know what the judge's background
OL,9,For education might be, but I'd imagine
OL,10,Fit would be different from mine!
OL,12,F"I'd like to be judged by my peer
OL,13,Fgroup, ordinary people... the kind of
OL,14,Fpeople who are my neighbours, the
OL,15,Fpeople I work with, who understand the
OL,16,Flife I live.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1779196276
OL,3,CDemonstration against scrapping of
OL,4,Cjury trials takes place
OL,6,F"Hold on to the jury service, support
OL,7,Fthe jury service, and make sure that
OL,8,Fordinary people are the ones who make
OL,9,Fthe final judgements on the kinds of
OL,10,Fpunishment people should get and
OL,11,Fwhether they're found guilty or not
OL,12,Fguilty. "
OL,14,FThe Government has previously argued
OL,15,Fthat reform to the justice system is
OL,16,Fneeded to reduce trial times, tackle
OL,17,Fbacklogs and achieve justice for
OL,18,Fvictims.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
