PN,35407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1779196276
OL,3,CDemonstration against scrapping of
OL,4,Cjury trials takes place
OL,6,FWhat other countries have non-jury
OL,7,Ftrials?
OL,9,FThe Channel Islands have always used
OL,10,Fnon-jury trials, and instead, cases
OL,11,Fare heard by judges or "jurats", known
OL,12,Fas lay judges.
OL,14,FGermany abolished them in 1924 and
OL,15,Fmost cases are tried by a panel made
OL,16,Fup of professional and lay judges,
OL,17,Fwhile the Netherlands have judge-only
OL,18,Ftrials.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
